Plyo Push-Up is a plyometric, bodyweight exercise designed to build power, strength, and speed in the upper body It is performed by starting in a regular push-up position and performing an explosive push-up, lifting the hands off the ground in the ascent and clapping or tapping the palms together and returning to the starting position This full body exercise is aimed at improving power, coordination, and agility, while also building the strength of the upper body muscles

The Close-Grip Hands-Elevated Push-Up is a great fitness movement for challenging shoulder and chest strength and overall body stability It is a variation of the traditional push-up and involves placing your hands closer together while elevating your upper body on a raised surface such as a box, bench, or step This variation increases difficulty and adds an extra challenge to the classic push-up, making it an ideal exercise for building upper body and core muscle strength and endurance

Suspended Push-Ups are a functional fitness exercise which combine elements of strength and stability training You perform the exercise by suspending yourself in a TRX strap or on elevated platforms like gymnastics rings and using your own bodyweight to perform the push-up This exercise helps to increase core strength, stability, and balance It can be adapted for all levels of fitness, from beginner to advanced

The Push Up To Side Plank fitness movement is an effective and dynamic full body exercise that targets muscles throughout the arms, shoulders, core, and back It is a compound movement involving a plank into a push-up and completed with a transition into a side plank This movement helps to build upper body and core strength, improve balance and stability, and also increases cardiovascular fitness

Isometric Chest Squeezes are a type of fitness movement that involves tensing and squeezing the chest muscles against a solid object like a wall or door frame This exercise helps promote muscular strength, body control, endurance, and stability, and is an effective training method for both athletes and regular exercisers

The Side-To-Side Push-Up is a fitness movement which works the arms, shoulders, and core muscles It requires you to perform multiple push-ups, variations of regular push-ups, and lateral motions It helps increase overall strength and is an exercise that can be done anywhere at any time

The Typewriter Push-Up is a fitness movement that involves alternating oneself between left and right while executing a modified push-up The push-up starts with the left arm extended straight and the right arm bent Then the body is pushed up as a normal push-up and then shifted to the right and back to the left, with each push-up This movement can be an effective way to build upper body strength and requires core stability and agility

Diamond Push-Up is a bodyweight exercise used to strengthen the chest, triceps, and shoulders It is performed by getting into a standard push-up position with the hands placed inside a triangle position, directly underneath the chest, instead of wider than shoulder width As the body is lowered towards the ground, the elbows should flare out to the sides, and the torso should be kept rigid as one press up for the desired repetitions

Judo Push-Up is a fitness movement that builds upper body strength while also developing core balance and proprioception It combines the traditional push-up with the judo breakfall technique to create a dynamic full-body workout The movement targets muscles in the chest, shoulders, and triceps while challenging balance and muscular stability

The Superman Push-Up is a full body exercise that focuses on strengthening the muscles in the arms, shoulders, back, chest, and core It is performed by getting into a standard push-up position, except during the up phase, the body should be lifted off the ground, reaching as high up as possible and fully extending the arms and back This exercise will help improve your core strength, balance and overall fitness

The Wide Push-Up is a fitness movement that strengthens the muscles of the chest, shoulders, and arms It is done by performing a standard push-up, but while keeping your arms wider than shoulder width apart This provides a new challenge that improves stability while also working out different muscles

The One-Arm Push-Up is an exercise that requires extreme coordination, balance, and physical strength It involves the use of just one arm to lower and raise the body, while the other arm is kept off the ground for added stability This exercise is beneficial for overall body strength and size, and it is a great way to work on core muscles

Clapping Push-Ups are a challenging plyometric exercise which involves pushing yourself up in the air from a regular push-up position, clapping your hands before returning to the ground for another rep They help to develop explosive power, build strength in the arms and chest muscles, and improve coordination

The Staggered Push-Up is a full body workout that involves doing a set of staggered push-ups - placing one hand slightly higher than the other - to challenge the muscles of the chest, arms, core, and legs It is an advanced variation of the traditional push-up, so it is recommended to only do this move if you have good core control and upper body strength

The Reverse-Grip Hands-Elevated Push-Up is an intense upper body exercise which targets multiple muscle groups It requires the individual to place their hands at a slightly wide stance on the ground with their fingers facing away from them, then raise the legs onto an elevated surface such as a chair or bench Once stable, the individual then lowers their body down by bending their elbows until their chest touches the ground, before pushing back up to the starting position This exercise utilizes the

Triple Clap Push-Ups are a modified version of the classic push-up exercise with added intensity from clapping at three different points during the exercise This movement not only increases difficulty but helps with coordination and arm strength while improving your overall fitness level

Side Kick-Through Push-Ups are a great full body exercise that combine strength and coordination This movement engages the core, shoulder, arms and legs to help develop muscular balance, and flexibility, and increase dynamic strength It is an exercise that makes use of a dynamic plyometric component to help you take your strength training to the next level

Swimming is a popular fitness activity that can provide a great total body workout It works the heart and lungs while engaging all major muscle groups Low impact and relatively safe for joint health, swimming offers a wide range of benefits, from improved cardiovascular fitness to increased strength and flexibility, and even stress relief

Fyr Push-Up is a challenging and creative fitness movement based on the traditional push up which incorporates various modifications and progressions It involves combining classic exercises such as push-ups, pikes, planks, shoulder taps, and burpees to create a full-body workout routine that increases muscle endurance, strength, and mobility

The Frog Push-Up is a fitness movement that targets multiple muscle groups including the chest, arms and core It utilizes a wide body position to produce increased stability and core strength while also strengthening the triceps and the chest The movement also aims to recruit more muscles than a traditional push-up, making it a great option for those looking to challenge themselves and build strength

The Wide Push-Up Plank Hold is a great fitness movement for developing overall strength and stability, as well as mobility It involves starting in a wide plank position and then pushing up into a push-up, lowering back down, and then maintaining the plank position for as long as possible It engages your lats, core, chest, shoulders, and arms to keep up good form and stability This exercise is great for sculpting and strengthening your body

Close Push-Ups are a type of bodyweight exercise that works the chest, arms, and core muscles This exercise consists of lowering and pushing one's body up and down using their own strength to lift and lower the body The additional challenge of bringing the hands closer together while performing the push-up makes the body work harder to complete the exercise and see results

The Push-Up ??Gethin Variation is a fitness movement developed by world-renowned personal trainer, Chris Gethin It involves taking the standard push-up and adding a dynamic element by exploding off the ground with each rep, going as high as possible for maximum plyometric benefit This variation can not only build strength and endurance in the chest muscles, but also helps to develop power and stability throughout the entire body

The Hm Incline Push-Up On Chair exercise is a dynamic full-body exercise that targets multiple muscle groups at once It focuses on building strength in the chest, triceps, and shoulders, while also engaging the core and lower body The exercise requires the use of a chair and a set of elevated feet for an added incline, which effectively challenges different stability and instability muscles for a more effective workout

Hm Push-Up is a fitness movement that is designed to challenge and build stability, strength, and mobility in the body The exercise consists of a regular push-up and then adding a hip lift at the end of each repetition It targets and produces strength in the chest, arms, shoulders, core, and lower back muscles and is great for all fitness levels

Hm Push-Plank is a popular full body fitness movement that works core muscles, improves posture, and increases overall stability This movement is based on a traditional plank, however it utilizes an added dynamic push up motion to challenge balance and engage more muscles It is designed to help practitioners burn fat while building strength and improving mobility

Am Chest Dips is an upper body strengthening exercise consisting of a series of dips performed with a straight body on a bar or bench It builds endurance and strength in the chest, shoulders, and triceps The benefits of the exercise come from its full range of motion and emphasis on pressing through the elbows as they move past the chest, working the entire anterior (frontal) musculature of the upper body

Push-ups are a very popular fitness movement that involves raising and lowering your body with your arms while keeping your back straight It is a full-body, compound exercise that works your arms, core, chest, abs, and lower body muscles all at once, making it an effective way to strengthen your body and build muscle

Up Push-Up is a fitness movement created with the intent to revolutionize the way people do traditional push-ups It uses an inclined position that enables people to push up from a lower starting point, making it easier and more comfortable to do push-ups The Up Push-Up encourages proper form through increased range of motion and challenges users to reach new heights in their fitness journey by engaging muscles not used in traditional push-ups

Un Push-Up is a fitness movement that encourages people to push themselves to the best of their ability It is designed to be completed within three minutes with minimal equipment and movement variations It focuses on performing a set of high-intensity exercises at maximum speed and attempts to minimize downtime Participants are encouraged to challenge themselves while remaining safe and sensible

Uns Foam Roll Pecs is a fitness movement combining foam rolling with dynamic and isometric stretching to focus on releasing tension in the pectoral muscles, allowing you to improve posture, flexibility, and range of motion This practice aims to restore shoulder health, address muscle imbalances, and enhance athletic performance

Un Hands Elevated Push-Up is an exercise variation of push-up movements designed to increase strength and flexibility in the body It involves pushing up and out of the push-up position while keeping your hands slightly elevated off the floor This variation is said to be easier on the wrists and shoulders, resulting in less stress and greater stability in the body for an efficient and effective push-up

The Holman Seal Drag To Push-Up fitness movement is a dynamic and challenging full body exercise that works to strengthen and tone the glutes, hamstrings, core, and arms simultaneously It gets its namesake from the motion of dragging a weight or resistance band to initiate the exercise, where the body is in the "seal" position Participants then proceed to a push-up while keeping the tension before returning to the "seal" position

Movements: Holman Hand-Elevated Push-Up With Hand Row

The Holman Push-Up is a fitness movement that focuses on building maximal strength in the upper body, core, and hips It is done by pushing off the ground into a plank position and then explosively coming back down, using the abdominal muscles to stabilize the core and the hip flexors to lift the legs into the air Holman Push-Ups are extremely beneficial for strengthening the surrounding muscles and increasing overall fitness

The Holman Slow Hips-Up Chest Press is an innovative fitness movement designed to focus on increasing strength and stability in the upper body It is a slow and controlled movement that focuses on gradually pressing the arms up and out against resistance, while also engaging the hips to ensure the body maintains an upright position This exercise targets the chest, shoulders, arms, and core muscles while also enhancing daily functional strength and stability

Movements: Holman Jump-Out Push-Up With Hand Hop Back

The Holman Push-Up To Sit Back is a fitness movement designed to strengthen the upper body and core while mobilizing the hips and shoulders It is a full body exercise that combines plyometrics, stability, and strength training to help improve shoulder and hip mobility The Holman Push-Up To Sit Back is a great addition to any fitness routine and can help you achieve better overall physical fitness

The Holman Sit Back Push-Up is a fitness movement developed by Australian fitness coach Grant Holman It is designed to work chest, core, and shoulder muscles while also improving muscular endurance and providing an intense workout Because the move requires the body to be suspended over the ground, holman sit back push-ups combine elements of strength and balance work for an effective, full-body exercise

The Holman Alternating Staggered Push-Up is a dynamic bodyweight exercise that strengthens and tones the chest, shoulders, and triceps muscles It involves alternating arms and shuffling legs in between each push up, adding a dynamic and challenging element to a standard push-up It is great for those looking to up the intensity level of their workouts while increasing strength, and is typically done in sets of 10-20 reps

Holman Foot-Up Diving Push-Up is an innovative full body exercise developed by fitness professionalWill Holman It works the upper and lower body together by combining high-intensity plyometric dips and powerful diving push-ups This exercise can be used to build strength, improve cardiovascular endurance and agility, and increase your power and explosiveness

The Holman Narrow Push-Up is a dynamic fitness movement that targets the full chest and triceps muscles It involves placing the hands close together on the floor, and performing a full range of motion push up - with the hands and arms as close together as comfortably possible throughout the exercise

The Holman Dynamo Push-Up is a variation of the traditional push-up that incorporates dynamic core and upper body strength movements to create a scoreable fitness challenge Repetitions of this whole body exercise incorporate upper body pushing, dynamic motion, and core stability that must be maintained while tapping each shoulder to the ground for a successful repetition

Holman Jump To Push-Up is a new fitness movement that combines dynamic jumping and traditional push-up movements It?™s designed to help increase power and explosiveness while also strengthening the core and upper body muscles The movement starts with a single leg jump to an elevated position followed by an explosive push-up This movement is perfect for those looking to build strength and power while improving overall body definition

The Holman Foot-Elevated Push-Up is a challenging full body exercise utilizing increased range of motion and gravity for maximum intensity The exercise uses an elevated platform to have the feet raised from the ground while in the push up position This allows for a deeper range of motion and forces the body to activate more muscles in the process The duration and the resistance can be scaled back or progressed depending on individual fitness levels

Total Fitness Plyo Push-Up is a fast-paced strength and conditioning exercise that builds explosive power and endurance This exercise involves jumping from a push-up position, pushing off the ground with your hands and extending your arms while jumping into the air The return to the ground requires a controlled and explosive push-up, transitioning from the airborne position back to the original push-up position This intense movement, when performed over a series of repetitions, builds muscle and helps burn calories

The Taylor Roll-Over Push-Up is a full-body exercise that uses the core, arms, back, and legs to improve overall fitness and muscle tone It is a dynamic yet challenging movement in which the participant starts in a push-up position and then rolls onto their upper back while lifting their legs in a total body crunch The movement is then reversed with the participant pushing back up into a full push-up on their hands and toes and finally finishing in an upright plank position

The Taylor One-Arm Push-Up Slow Negative is a unique fitness movement that involves holding one arm up in the air and then pushing your body up and down from the ground, using only that one arm and slowing down the motion as you lower your body This movement strengthens the muscles around the shoulder, abdomen, and back, helping to improve overall upper body strength

30 Chest Push-Up To Isometric Hold is a fitness movement that utilizes full-body engagement to build strength and power This push-up variation requires you to hold yourself in the up position of a push-up for an isometric hold before returning to the starting position for one repetition This movement helps to develop strength in the upper body, core, and legs and can be modified to fit any fitness level

30 Chest Push-Ups is a fitness movement that involves pushing your body up and down from a lying position on the floor in a repetitive motion This movement helps to improve strength and tone your chest muscles It can be made more challenging by varying the number of reps and/or the type of push-up used With regular practice, you can build a toned chest and strong upper body

The 30 Chest Bench Push-Up is an effective full-body exercise that can help increase strength and stability This simple movement requires you to start in a prone position, hands shoulder-width apart and feet supported by a bench From there, push your body up and back for 30 repetitions, ensuring full range of motion on both the up and downward phases of the movement This is a great exercise for building overall strength, upper body endurance, and core stability

Metaburn 3-Phase Push-Up is an innovative fitness regimen that incorporates both strength training and cardio It is based on a series of push-up variations designed to build strength and endurance, as well as to stimulate fat burning This program is great for those looking for an efficient way to get in shape without overdoing it

Metaburn Fast Feet To Push-Up is a functional fitness movement that combines fast feet and push-ups This movement consists of quickly alternating stepping from one foot to the other in an athletic stance while keeping the arms in a push-up position This movement targets the entire body, especially the core, chest, and lower body muscles It is an effective way to promote cardiovascular endurance and muscular strength, and is a great way to elevate your heart rate while also building a strong foundation

Movements: Metaburn Judo Push-Up To Pike Push-Up

The Metaburn Pike Push-Up is a full-body fitness movement that challenges the core, arms, and chest You begin in a plank position, then lower yourself into a pike hold, press your body up, and lower again This exercise serves to develop total-body strength, and increase balance and coordination

Metaburn Push-Up To Frogger is a fitness movement designed to target both the upper and lower body It combines a traditional push-up with the bodyweight movement of a frogger This makes it one of the most dynamic full-body exercises available, as it provides a great cardio workout while also engaging a variety of different muscle groups

The Metaburn Push-Up With Hand Side-Step is a fitness movement that combines a basic push-up with a side-step exercise It works both your upper body muscles and core, while also improving balance and coordination This challenging exercise is a great way to burn extra calories and get your heart rate up, making it an effective way to improve your overall physical fitness level

Metaburn Push-Up With Hand-Up Rotation is a challenging, full body exercise that combines push-ups with hand-up rotations to target multiple muscle groups, boost muscular endurance, and rev up metabolism This exercise requires a high level of coordination and strength and is great for burning calories, improving your athleticism, and sculpting the upper body

The Metaburn Sphinx Push-Up is a unique fitness movement that combines elements from both dynamic Pilates and traditional push-ups It requires participants to keep their core engaged while using their arms and back to push their body away from the floor and up into the air It helps to make the body stronger, increases endurance, and builds core and upper body strength It is an all-in-one exercise and is perfect for those looking to up their fitness game

The Metaburn Spiderman Push-Up is a full body compound movement designed to boost functional strength and increase metabolic rate It targets the core, chest, arms, back, and shoulders, and involves pushing up and extending the leg to one side while loaded under a weight or resistance band This combines the elements of a classic push-up with dynamic and powerful mobility movements to make it a great alternative for a full-body workout

The 15-Rep Push-Up is an exercise technique that helps to increase strength and improve shoulder stability The 15-Rep is performed by starting in the standard push-up position, lowering the body halfway down, rising back up to the starting position, and then lowering back down all the way to the floor This extra range of motion helps to develop stronger muscles and increase shoulder stability, which are important for overall physical fitness

Cross-Over Push-Ups are a challenging fitness movement that involve pushing and pulling your body up and down while rotating your arms across your chest This exercise works your arms, shoulders, chest and core and can be done with either a full range of motion or a single repetition with a pause at the top and bottom

The Leverage Incline Chest Press is an effective compound movement for developing strength and size in the chest, shoulders, and triceps This exercise is done with a leverage machine that forces the user to push off a platform at an incline angle Performing multiple reps of this exercise helps to improve shoulder stability and core strength, while increasing the size of the chest, triceps, and deltoids

Butterfly is a full-body workout and fitness movement that focuses on activating multiple muscle groups at the same time It utilizes dynamic movements and resistance training to help improve balance, strength, and stability while encouraging mindful movement and breath awareness Butterfly focuses on improving body composition, building strength, and maintaining a healthy lifestyle

The Decline Smith Press is a popular fitness exercise that works the chest, shoulder, and triceps muscles It is a multi-joint, compound exercise that involves using a Smith Machine with a weighted barbell to press a bar from a low-incline or decline position to a fully extended, lockout position where the arms are straight By manipulating the barbell's angle, the decline Smith Press can be a great way to add variety to traditional flat or incline presses

The Smith Machine Bench Press is a popular fitness movement that involves using a Smith Machine, typically with a built-in barbell and adjustable weights, and performing an incline chest press while lying on a bench It is a great exercise for building strength and size in the chest, triceps, and shoulder muscles

Smith Machine Decline Press is a great exercise and fitness movement for toning, strengthening and sculpting the muscles in the chest, shoulders and arms It involves lowering a barbell down to the lowest possible point on a decline bench, usually bringing it to chest or neck level while keeping the back flat and core and glutes engaged It is an excellent way to build strength and stability in the chest, shoulders and arms, while also providing numerous training benefits

Machine Bench Press is a fitness movement that focuses on strengthening the chest and triceps muscles It is performed on a machine that provides resistance as you push up and down This movement helps to improve strength, increase muscular endurance, and build muscle size

The Smith Machine Push-Up is a type of bodyweight exercise that requires use of a Smith Machine This exercise targets the chest, arms, and core muscles while challenging the body's stability It is an excellent exercise to increase strength and improve posture and body alignment

The Holman Slow Deadlift is a fitness movement that is designed to strengthen and activate the muscles of the lower body and improve balance and stability This deadlifting technique requires a more controlled and slower effort than traditional deadlifting to allow for greater time under tension and to lessen the risk of injury It involves using a narrower stance, dropping down to the ground with the bar in the hands, and coming back up without the use of a bounce or momentum This technique also helps to build mental

The Holman Deadlift to Overhead Press is a full body strength training exercise that combines deadlifts and overhead presses ??two of the most effective exercises for building total body strength and muscular size The movement, created by CrossFit legend Greg Holman, engages the entire body and requires great coordination and core stability Its great for sculpting strong shoulders and strengthening the lats, quads, hamstrings, and glutes

The Holman Staggered-Stance Deadlift is a powerful lower-body strength-building exercise It's a modification of the conventional straight-leg deadlift that involves placing one foot behind the other with staggered feet This stance activates the gluteal muscles and hip abductors with the goal of improving core stability and balance for a more efficient workout

The Holman Deadlift to Front Raise is a fitness movement that helps strengthen your entire body and build core strength in one exercise This movement is performed in a seated position and involves lifting a barbell from the ground to your chest, then lifting it up over your head and into a front raise at shoulder height This exercise works your glutes, hamstrings, quadriceps, and core muscles, giving you an overall workout when done correctly and safely

The Holman Deadlift To Chest Press is a compound exercise that combines two very effective exercises: deadlifting and chest pressing It involves lifting a weight off the ground and holding it against your chest before explosively performing a chest press It targets the entire body and works the muscles of both the upper and lower body, making it an effective full-body workout

The Holman Deadlift To Squat Thrust movement is a full body, strength and conditioning workout that focuses on explosiveness, power, and core stability This exercise combines a deadlift and a squat thrust, creating a combination exercise that works almost every muscle in the body It is an efficient exercise for developing strength and conditioning, and can be an effective workout for all fitness levels

The Holman Deadlift To Biceps Curl is a hybrid fitness movement that combines both a deadlift and a biceps curl It works both the lower back and biceps muscles at the same time in a single dynamic movement, and is a great way to build strength, muscular control, and stability throughout your entire body

The Dumbbell Kickstand Deadlift is a great full-body fitness movement that develops overall strength and stability It works the muscles of the legs, glutes, and lower back while challenging your balance, coordination, and core strength This movement not only helps build functional strength, but can also burn calories and increase metabolism

Thesingle-leg stiff-legged deadlift to row is a dynamic and challenging exercise that helps to strengthen the core and lower back muscles while also engaging the upper back muscles and improving balance and coordination It is an excellent way of targeting the posterior chain in a comprehensive way and can help to improve posture and overall physical fitness

Fyr2 Dumbbell Deadlift is a fitness movement that focuses on strengthening the entire posterior chain while incorporating core stability and balance This exercise works the hamstrings, glutes, back muscles, and abdominal muscles for a complete full-body workout It can be performed with a pair of dumbbells of moderate to heavy weight This particular exercise engages multiple muscle groups and is an effective way to build overall strength

Movements: Fyr2 Dumbbell Deadlift To Dumbbell Upright Row
Desc: Fyr2 Dumbbell Deadlift to Dumbbell Upright Row is an effective and efficient full-body workout that focuses on strengthening the entire muscle chain by combining an exercise for the lower body (a deadlift) with one for the upper body (an upright row) This workout will engage both your muscles and your core in order to develop pure strength, balance, coordination, and dynamic movement

Atlas Stones, also known as Hercules Stones, is a strength-training movement originating from the Highland Games of Scotland It involves lifting a large round stone, ranging from 12kg - 158kg in weight, off the ground and onto a raised platform using only the body's strength It requires excellent body control, coordination and power, and has become a popular exercise among fitness enthusiasts looking to challenge themselves in novel ways

The Axle Deadlift is a full-body strength-training exercise that builds muscular strength and endurance in the upper and lower body This exercise involves lifting an Axle barbell from the ground up to hips level while keeping a stable posture and stiff spine It primarily works the posterior chain muscles such as the glutes, hamstrings, back, abdominals, and rhomboids This full-body exercise also allows for more intense loading and can be progressed as you become stronger

Atlas Stone Trainer is a fitness movement that focuses on utilizing the common strength training equipment, the atlas stone, to build full body strength This program provides guidance for proper form and technique to maximize the effectiveness of the atlas stone, as well as programming to develop overall strength, power, and conditioning The program is adaptable for all fitness levels and includes progressive training to ensure continued progress

Partner Flat-Bench Back Extension is an exercise to develop strength and muscle tone in the lower back region This exercise requires two people with one person lying on a flat bench on their stomach, and the other person needs to straddle the lower back area of the person on the bench and lift up their legs and hips up and down This can be done with light weights or without weights to develop the lower back muscles

Keg Load is a unique, full-body exercise movement created to develop strength, balance, and endurance It is based on an ancient Russian strongman training method and involves performing exercises with a keg filled with either sand, stones, or water, that can be manipulated in various ways to work the entire body in an interesting and effective way

Partner Bench Back Extension is a fitness movement consisting of two partners lying on a bench with their feet together so that one person is supporting their own upper body and the other person is supporting both their own and the partner's Each partner then takes turns raising and extending their legs outwards whilst the other partner keeps them down with their hands This exercise helps to increase flexibility and strength in the back muscles

The Rack Pull - Gethin Variation is a fitness movement that involves setting up your barbell on a suitable rack and pulling the bar up to the lower abdomen and hips while maintaining a neutral back position This exercise targets the entire posterior chain, working the glutes, hamstrings, and lower back muscles, and developing explosive power, strength, and stability

The Hex Bar Deadlift - Gethin Variation is a strength-building exercise that focuses on developing a strong posterior chain and core muscles It involves a hexagonal-shaped barbell, which the lifter stands inside and grasps handles that are parallel to their thighs, enabling them to keep their spine in a neutral position while performing the lift This movement emphasizes proper form and function, allowing for greater range of motion while reducing the risk of injury

The Holman Deadlift is a fitness movement designed to improve lower-body strength and stability It consists of a traditional deadlift movement with an arched back position to reduce strain on the lumbar spine, and utilizes special breathing techniques to increase core activation and improve power output Additionally, a modified grip is used to better engage the back muscles The Holman Deadlift can be a great addition to any strength routine, helping to build muscle and improve athletic performance

Acft Low-Handle Trap Bar Deadlift is a form of exercise which focuses on working the entire body by using a low-handle trap bar This movement consists of lifting the weighted bar from the ground and returning it to its original position It is beneficial in building strength and balance by working the legs, glutes, lower back, core, upper back, and even the arms It also improves balance and coordination, making it a great exercise for both competitive and recreational athletes

The Neutral-Grip Lat Pull-Down is an effective strength-training movement that targets the back muscles, particularly the latissimus dorsi and biceps By using a pronated or supinated grip to hold onto the bar, the movement works the shoulders and back muscles in a safe and effective manner Additionally, it allows for more natural and comfortable along with more comprehensive development of muscles in the shoulders, back, and core

The Seated Cable Deadlift is a compound movement that targets the upper body while engaging the arms, shoulders, and back It is a low impact exercise that works to increase strength and stability throughout the torso and stabilizing muscle groups in the upper body

The Cable Stiff-Legged Deadlift is a great movement for building strength and stability within the posterior chain (glutes, hamstrings, and lower back) It requires precision body mechanics to keep the spine in a neutral alignment while engaged in the lift The main purpose of this exercise is to isolate and activate the hamstring muscles but it also helps to develop core stability and power

The Single-Leg Cable Stiff-Legged Deadlift is a functional fitness exercise used to build strength and stability in the glutes, hamstrings, and core It involves stabilizing the core while balancing and lifting a single-leg using a cable or band, thus providing an effective isolation movement to target specific muscle groups It is a great exercise for athletes and fitness enthusiasts looking to improve balance, power, and body composition

Unbanded Dumbbell Romanian Deadlifts (RDLs) is a lower body and core exercise that requires proper form and core strength as you stand with feet hip-width apart while holding two dumbbells with an overhand grip by your sides The movement involves hinging from the hips, and while keeping the back flat, reach down to the floor and lift the weights back up to your starting position to effectively target the glutes, hamstrings, quads, and core

Seated Back Extension is a great way to strengthen and tone the lower back muscles It involves sitting on a stable chair or bench and slowly extending your back and relaxing in the starting position It is beneficial for improving posture, spinal alignment, and core strength Furthermore, it helps to reduce the amount of stress placed on the spine and can be used for general lower back fitness

Back Extension is a fitness movement that strengthens and increases flexibility of the lower back muscles and promotes spinal alignment It involves bent-over exercises that use a bench, stability ball, exercise bands, Swiss balls, or other fitness equipment to lengthen the spine in a controlled manner and target hind-muscles It can help reduce injuries, relieve stress, and improve overall health and well-being

Hyperextensions with no hyperextension bench is a type of workout designed to strengthen the muscles of the lower back and core It is performed without the use of a hyperextension bench, instead focusing on core stabilization and strength It is a dynamic and challenging exercise that can help trainees build a strong, healthy core and back that are stable and resistant to injury

Superman is a full-body exercise that requires you to lay flat on your stomach, arms straight above you, and your legs straight behind you, your body and limbs forming the shape of Superman's "S" emblem As you raise your torso and arms completely off the ground, you strengthen your core muscles, glutes, and hips to hold and maintain the position This is a great exercise for core strength, core stability, and awareness of your body

Hug a Ball is a fitness movement created to encourage people to stay active Through the use of weighted medicine balls, users can enjoy full-body exercises that incorporate mobility, stability, and strength training in one session The program is highly scalable for both beginners and elites alike, assuring that all levels can benefit from the program

Child's Pose is a yoga-inspired fitness regimen that focuses on breathing, stretching, and strengthening exercises to build strength, balance, and flexibility It works to activate the body, increase mobility, and improve posture, and can be done in the comfort of your home or at a gym This movement is an excellent choice for both first-timers and experienced yogis alike

Pelvic Tilt Into Bridge is a fitness movement that helps to improve spinal health and core stability It involves lowering the back by tucking the tailbone, then gently lifting the lower back into an exaggerated arch while keeping the pelvis tilted This exercise helps to strengthen the abdominal muscles while also activating the gluteal muscles, resulting in improved posture, spinal stability, and core strength

Hug Knees to Chest is a simple yet effective fitness movement used to strengthen and stretch the abdominal muscles It involves slowly bringing the knees up to the chest while inhaling deeply and then returning them to the starting position while exhaling This exercise can be done either with legs straight or bent and is often used as part of a warm up routine or for toning

Pyramid is a fitness movement designed to help people build strength and endurance through a variety of exercises, rep ranges, and times The pyramid consists of a series of sets performed with increasing intensity, so the intensity increases with each set It's an effective way to push your body and help reach fitness goals

Partner Superman With Alternating High-Five is a high-intensity, partner-based exercise that requires alternating high-fives between two people, with the goal of improving strength, coordination, and cardiovascular endurance It incorporates the Superman exercise, where the participants lie down on their stomach with arms and legs outstretched, raise their chest and legs off the ground in a 'flying' position and hold for time The exercise is repeated multiple times, alternating high-fives with a partner

Hyperextension - Gethin Variation is a core exercise specifically targeting the posterior chain muscles of the back and legs It is performed using a traditional hyperextension bench that is slightly angled to increase body tension and engagement with the core muscles, while adding instability to the movement It helps build strength, stability, and mobility around the hip, back, and core muscles, while developing strong glutes, hamstrings, and lower back muscles

The Back Extension - Gethin Variation is a great exercise for strengthening the lower back and core muscles This exercise consists of lying face down on a flat bench with arms outstretched and a foam roller or medicine ball placed behind the head, and then using the lower back muscles to lift the upper body with arms still extended into the air This exercise is an excellent choice for anyone looking to strengthen their lower back and build better functional fitness

Hm Banana Stretch is a fitness movement that focuses on whole-body strength and flexibility It combines stretching with functional exercises, utilizing monkey bars, rings, boxes, and other fun tools to challenge users while also providing a variety of low-impact, low-intensity variations It emphasizes good form, technique, and engagement of the core and has the potential to help target problem areas while increasing mobility, stability, and overall body composition

Hm T-Spine Stretch On Wall is a fantastic fitness movement that focuses on stretching the muscles of the upper back and spine It utilises a wall for support, allowing participants to focus on their breathing and form to create the desired tension in the desired muscles This movement helps to provide relief from back and neck pain, promote greater range of motion, and improve overall posture for long-term results

Hm Child's Pose is a fitness movement designed to promote physical and mental wellbeing It is an accessible yoga pose that can be done anywhere, anytime, and is a great way to reduce stress, awaken the body, and open up body energy It can be used as part of a larger yoga practice, as a transition move between poses, or as a relaxation technique to incorporate into daily life

Hm Cobra is a fitness movement founded by former US Navy SEAL Marcus Luttrell It focuses on three different exercises: hip mobility, core strength, and shoulder stability The program is designed to help you build strength, endurance, and agility in your entire body It consists of a mix of body weight exercises, plyometrics, and corrective exercises to build power, stability, and mobility

Hm Cobra With Arm Retraction is a challenging workout designed to strengthen the core and upper body It combines elements of yoga and martial arts, requiring strength, balance, flexibility, and coordination as you curl the back, press your bellybutton into the spine, and lift your arms away from the floor, repeating this dynamic for a powerful, full body workout

The Hm Dive-Bomber is a great full body exercise that improves strength and conditioning, increases power and stability, and builds endurance It is a total body movement that requires athletes to use the entire body to move as quickly and powerfully as possible An athlete must plunge into a deep squat and then drive their hands and feet as hard as they can The exercise requires the coordination of several muscle groups and helps to train speed and power

The Hm Downward-Facing Dog Pose is an exercise move focusing on strengthening and stretching the entire body It is a great way to improve posture, work on core strength, and build endurance This pose is a mainstay of yoga exercises, and can be done at any level, from the beginner to the expert It helps to improve flexibility in the shoulders, hamstrings, and back while also elevating the heart rate for a calorie-burning boost

Movements: Hm Downward Dog To Left Leg Extension To Warrior Pose
Desc: The fitness movement 'Hm Downward Dog To Left Leg Extension To Warrior Pose' is a combination of three yoga poses, designed to stretch the hamstrings, calves and hips while strengthening the core and arms It starts with the Downward Dog pose, then extends the left leg up and out, pressing into the heel to increase the stretch Finally, the movement finishes up with the Warrior Pose, which challenges balance and focus while toning the stomach and legs

Hm Spine Twist is a fitness movement designed to increase mobility and strengthen the core It involves twisting the spine and using active range of motion to stretch and strengthen the key muscles associated with the core It also helps to improve overall posture and body mechanics, and can be used to target problem areas in the lower back, mid-back, and upper back

Hm Rag Doll is a fitness movement inspired by Pilates, yoga, and functional fitness It builds strength and increases range of motion with a focus on alignment and mindful movement This fitness method combines the art of body weight, balance, and creative movement sequences to create a unique and fun workout experience

Superman is a comprehensive fitness movement that challenges the whole body with dynamic, compound movements It incorporates core conditioning, agility, balance, strength, power, flexibility, and coordination to provide an intense, adaptable workout

Weighted Back Extension is a fitness movement used to strengthen one's lower back and torso muscles It is an exercise that is performed while lying on one's stomach, and then arching or extending the back and torso while holding a weight such as a medicine ball or dumbbell This exercise also works the muscles in the shoulders and biceps

Metaburn Swimmer is a fitness movement that focuses on a combination of bodyweight exercises and swimming drills that are designed to improve both strength and cardio endurance, thus optimizing metabolic performance in athletes of any level It offers challenging workouts that can be tailored to the individual?™s fitness level and goals, and can be applied to a number of sports or activities

Dancer's Stretch is a fitness movement that focuses on improving and maintaining flexibility and mobility through a series of dynamic and static postures and stretches It is designed to relieve tension and stress in the body while simultaneously building strength, core stability and balance The combination of dance movements and stretches make it a fun and effective way to improve overall health and wellbeing

Cat Stretch is an exercise which involves arching and curling the spine as if imitating a cat It is meant to not only lengthen and strengthen your spine, but to also improve balance, coordination, and overall flexibility It is done mainly on all fours and consists of alternating rounds of arching and curling your back while inhaling and exhaling the entire time

The Crossover Reverse Lunge is a fitness movement that incorporates lunging, twisting, and dynamic trunk stabilisation to engage and strengthen your core, glutes, quads, and hamstrings It is a great exercise to add into any workout routine to promote balance, stability, and proper alignment in the body

Standing Pelvic Tilt is a fitness movement that targets the core muscles and helps to improve posture This movement involves holding your core tight by pressing your hips forward and tucking your tailbone down while maintaining a straight spine This is done while standing, and the core muscles are activated throughout the body as this pose is held for an extended period of time This exercise can be done as a part of a regular exercise routine either at home or in the gym, and can help to improve

Exercise ball weighted hyperextension is an effective lower back exercise used for strengthening the core, glutes, and hamstrings, and can also be used for increasing flexibility It is a type of bodyweight exercise that involves kneeling on an elevated exercise ball and slowly bending forward and backward in order to activate the muscles in the back This exercise is often done with an extra weight, which adds extra resistance and increases muscle challenge

Exercise Ball Rear Delt Fly is an upper-body strengthening exercise targeting the muscles of the posterior shoulder and upper back It requires a medicine ball or dumbbell, placed slightly underneath the chest while lying on an exercise ball The arms are extended backward, in a fly-like fashion, then brought back up to the starting position with control This exercise helps to develop stability, posture, and range of motion in the shoulder and upper back muscles while also allowing for varied levels of intensity

The Lying Rear Delt Y is a simple yet effective fitness movement meant to strengthen and tone the sides of the shoulders (the rear deltoids) It is performed lying face down on a weight bench while holding a pair of dumbbells in each hand Pointing the elbows out to the sides, raise the arms up towards the ceiling in a Y formation Then lower the arms back down This exercise helps build strength, definition, and stability in the shoulder region

Movements: Partner Facing Feet-Elevated Side Plank With Band Row
Desc: Partner Facing Feet-Elevated Side Plank With Band Row is a dynamic partner stability exercise that focuses on core strength and stability Utilizing the stability of the side plank, and an anchored resistance band, from a raised position the partner will pull the band towards their midsection maintaining the side plank position, while their partner supplements them with resistance This exercise provides a comprehensive total body workout that helps to strengthen the core, shoulders, back and arms

Partner Side Plank Band Row is an effective and challenging fitness movement for two people One partner is in a side plank position with both arms extended, while the other partner stands perpendicular, holding one end of a resistance band in each hand The rower is then required to perform alternating rows against resistance, training their entire upper body during the motion It is a great way to build strength and stability for both partners

The Band-Assisted Chin-Up is a popular fitness movement used to increase overall body strength and endurance It involves looping a resistance band around a pull-up bar and then placing one or both feet in the band The band provides assistance, allowing the user to complete full chin-ups more easily by taking some of the weight off their body It is an effective way to build muscle, improve posture, and enhance overall fitness

The 30 Back Reverse-Grip Band-Assisted Pull-Up is an effective exercise for building strength and endurance in the upper body It combines the traditional pull-up with resistance bands for added assistance and introduces an extra level of difficulty by requiring the user to pull up with an overhand grip This targeted, yet challenging, exercise is an ideal addition to a workout routine and perfect for increasing muscular endurance

Band Bent-Over Rows are an excellent exercise to help strengthen the back muscles and improve posture This movement involves holding a resistance band in both hands at about waist height while bending your knees and lowering your chest to the ground You then pull the band up while maintaining a neutral spine, keeping your arms close to your body This exercise is great for targeting the back muscles and improving general strength

The reverse-grip bent-over row is a strength training exercise that targets the back muscles, specifically the lats, traps, and rhomboids This movement is usually performed with a barbell, but dumbbells can also be used It entails bending at the hips with a slight arch in the back while maintaining a flat back and feet shoulder-width apart The elbows are then held close to the body while the weight is pulled up toward the chest It is an

The One-Arm Long Bar Row is an exercise that focuses on strengthening the back and shoulders by using a long barbell or a cable machine It is done with one arm at a time, pulling the barbell towards the lower ribs or lifting the handle in a rowing motion It is a great movement for developing muscular back strength and core stability

The Bent over Barbell Row is a compound fitness movement which strengthens multiple muscle groups in the back and arms It specifically targets the mid and lower trapezius, teres major and latissimus dorsi It is performed by hinging at the waist and gripping the barbell with an overhand grip The athlete then pulls the barbell up to their upper abdominal region and lowering back down with control until arms are fully extended

The Yates Row Reverse Grip is a fitness movement designed and popularized by British professional bodybuilder and powerlifter Dorian Yates It is a rowing exercise that uses an overhand grip on the barbell to target the upper back muscles, with the goal of increasing strength and muscle mass in this area

Pendlay Row, named after Coach Glen Pendlay, is a strength training exercise focusing on building lean muscle mass and core strength It is often used to develop back, shoulder, trap, and bicep muscles, requiring the user to explosively lift a weight up from the floor as if they were performing a row, maintaining a flat back and neutral spine to ensure proper form

Straight Bar Bench Mid Rows is a fitness movement exercise used to strengthen the upper back and arms It is done by kneeling on a bench with a straight bar or dumbbell held in front of you, palms facing down, and then pulling the weight back towards your chest while keeping your back straight The exercise will help build increased strength and stability in the back and arms, while also contributing to general fitness

Barbell Seal Row is a strengthening exercise used to increase upper body strength and muscle mass It is done standing with feet slightly wider than hip-width apart and the barbell held in front of the hips The back should remain straight and the arms extended as the barbell is pulled up towards the chest Lower slowly with control for maximum results

Yates Row is a strength training exercise developed by coach and former bodybuilder Mike Yates It involves a bent-over barbell row while leaning forward at a 45-degree angle, emphasizing the use of both arms to pull the weight up This exercise targets the upper back, lats, middle back and traps, and is great for bulking up and building overall strength

Plate Row is a fitness movement designed to be a low-impact total-body workout It uses your own body weight and a weighted plate, which is held between your legs while you?™re in a standing position This movement allows you to work out your entire body by performing controlled yet dynamic movements that involve rowing, push-pulling and pressing It is a great exercise for people of all fitness levels and gaining strength, muscle, and balance

Single-Arm Landmine Row is a strength training exercise that involves hinging the body to one side, and extending the arm holding a barbell out from the shoulder to engage muscles in the back, chest, and arms It works the core stabilizing muscles along with the muscles of the upper body to develop balanced and functional strength

The Tbs T-bar Row is a strength-training exercise which helps to build the lats, rhomboids, traps, and core muscles It involves gripping handles attached to a barbell, then straddling the bar with feet hip-width apart and pushing the bar away from the chest The exercise increases upper body strength and improves stability and posture

The Tbs Deficit Deadlift is an advanced resistance training exercise that involves using heavier weights and a deeper exercise range of motion to engage more muscles, thus increasing the intensity of the exercise and facilitating greater muscle growth and strength This exercise involves using a barbell, lifting it off the floor with an increased range of motion, and returning the bar back to the floor after each rep It is an effective full-body strength exercise that helps build strength, power, and muscle all at once

The Bent-Over Barbell Row - Gethin Variation is an exercise focused on developing the back muscles by bending over and rowing a barbell up and down the body with your hands It is an exclusive form of bent-over barbell rows and emphasizes safety and efficacy as it puts less strain on the lower back Using the Gethin Variation technique also allows for increased range of motion and responsibility for the back muscles, and is especially effective for those with poor flexibility

The Barbell Bent-Over Row is an excellent exercise for building overall upper body strength and size It primarily works the back muscles, as well as the biceps and shoulders It requires stabilization of the core and leg muscles and is one of the most effective compound exercises for developing general strength and muscular balance

Un Barbell Scrape The Rack is a fitness movement which emphasizes form on compound exercises such as squats, deadlifts, presses, and rows It was designed to help individuals focus on form and increase their chances of successful execution of an exercise By scraping the plate across the rack, it creates auditory feedback that helps with tempo and keeps lifters honest to their form Additionally, it improves stability and helps build mental toughness

The Barbell Deadlift Bent-Over Row Complex is a full-body strength and conditioning workout It combines the traditional barbell deadlift, bent-over row, and bent-over reverse fly exercises into one powerful exercise that targets large muscle groups for increased muscle endurance and overall strength This challenging exercise not only helps to build the lower body, but it also helps to develop the core, upper back, and arms for a well-rounded strength building experience

30 Back Barbell Deadlift is a popular fitness movement designed to increase overall posterior chain strength and hypertrophy It involves gripping a barbell with an overhand grip and lifting it up to the maximum height allowed by your back The weight should be heavy enough to be challenging and should be composed of multiple sets of 30 total repetitions It is a great workout for building core strength and stability as well as improving muscular endurance

The 30 Back Bent-Over Barbell Row is a great exercise for strengthening the lat muscles of the back, increasing overall upper body strength and stability It involves bending over while gripping the barbell, then driving up with your back, keeping the back straight and pulling the barbell towards your chest Each rep should be slow and controlled, and maintained for at least 30 seconds, ensuring that you are getting the most out of the exercise

30 Back T-Bar Row is a total body movement that involves strength and mobility to achieve increased core strength and back muscle activation The movement targets the lats, rhomboids, traps and other back muscles, enabling increased power and efficiency in everyday lifting and exercise This exercise requires controlled form with minimal momentum to ensure maximum muscle engagement

The 30 Back Underhand Bent-Over Barbell Row is a strength and fitness movement that helps to improve back strength and postural stability The exercise is performed with an underhand grip, where an athlete bends at the waist and pulls a resistance weight towards their abdomen with the arms extended It is a great exercise to target the back muscles and build strength and stability in the posterior chain of the body

Kettlebell Alternating Renegade Row is a great exercise to build strength and core stability The exercise involves holding two kettlebells in a push-up position and alternating arms while rowing each kettlebell up to the side of the chest The movement challenges your core and gives you a full-body workout while pushing your cardio endurance

The King Maker Weighted Jump Squat is a popular fitness movement designed to strengthen the core, legs and glutes as well as promote improved agility and balance It involves performing a deep jump squat with added weight held close to the chest and then jumping explosively to full extension, ensuring the core remains braced throughout the movement This exercise can be used to build power and performance as well as mobility and coordination

The 3D Dumbbell Lunge is a type of functional strength training exercise that works on multiple muscle groups It is an intense full-body movement that challenges the core and builds strength and stability, while developing both lower and upper body strength It is designed to be a total body exercise by engaging the entire kinetic chain, while challenging coordination and balance

The Metaburn Dumbbell Burpee is a powerful full-body workout combining aerobic and resistance training It works by combining the two exercises of a burpee and a dumbbell press This is done by bending down to perform a burpee followed by a dumbbell press while standing This movement will help to raise your heart rate, torch calories and build strength all in one exercise

Dumbbell Jump Squat with Rotation is a dynamic exercise that combines full-body movement and power to target your quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, core muscles, and shoulders The movement works by incorporating a jump while simultaneously performing a rotating trunk movement, which increases force output and overall difficulty This complex exercise is an effective way to build strength, power, and stability throughout the entire body

Movements: Metaburn Dumbbell Wide Squat To Rack

Movements: Metaburn Reverse Lunge To High Pull

Movements: Metaburn Reverse Lunge With Overhead Raise

The 30 Legs Dumbbell Squat is an intense yet rewarding full-body workout that targets both the lower and upper body This challenging movement consists of holding two dumbbells in the air while squatting, alternating the side with each rep to ensure an even distribution of the weight With each rep, your hips are pushed back and your chest rises while you lower yourself to a 90-degree angle and then return back up This movement encourages core strength and balance while engaging the glutes

The Dumbbell Step-Down Reverse Lunge is an excellent fitness movement for developing lower body strength and core stability It involves steadying the torso while keeping the chest up while holding a pair of dumbbells and stepping one leg back and lowering your body down until the back knee is just above the ground The front leg remains bent at a 90-degree angle and the back leg is straight Then stand back up by pressing through the front heel and repeat the same motion

Tire Flip is an intense fitness movement that involves lifting and flipping a large tire using strength and momentum It is an explosive exercise that works the entire body, helping to increase grip strength, cardiovascular endurance, and power The tire can either be flipped with both hands in a standing position, or with one hand in a bent-over position

Single Leg Push-Off is a functional fitness exercise which challenges core activation and balance while building strength in the lower body It is performed by standing on one leg and pushing off with the opposing leg against a wall, side, or other stable surface This movement trains the muscles of the lower body, including the hip flexors, glutes, and hamstrings, while simultaneously targeting the deep core muscles for improved balance and coordination

The Bear Crawl Sled Drag is a full-body, high intensity, functional fitness exercise that combines the core-strengthening bear crawl movement while dragging a sled to build endurance and explosive power It works the entire body while building balance, coordination, and stability, as you will be using your entire body to propel the sled

Bicycling is a popular fitness movement that is beneficial for physical as well as mental health It is a low-impact type of exercise that provides a variety of health benefits, including improved cardiovascular fitness, improved muscle strength and flexibility, and weight loss It is also a great way to get out and enjoy nature, and it can provide a great sense of accomplishment

The Hex-Bar Deadlift is a fitness movement that uses an angled hexagonal barbell designed to reduce stress on the lower back It strengthens the back muscles, glutes, and hamstrings while reducing the risk of injury compared to traditional deadlifts It is a great exercise to include in any full-body exercise program, as it works multiple muscle groups simultaneously

Skating is a type of fitness movement that involves moving through a continuous sequence of steps, jumps, spins and turns, while performing a series of movements on skates with the intent to evoke a feeling of joy and freedom It can be enjoyed by people of all ages and can offer a fun form of exercise as well as an exciting way to express your creativity

Weighted Sissy Squat is a exercise that helps target glutes and quads It requires the use of a squat rack and a weight bar The movement starts by placing both feet flat on the floor and placing the weight bar on the back of the shoulders The hips are pushed backwards, keeping the feet firmly grounded, and the movement ends by bringing the torso to a vertical position This exercise requires proper form and balance

Yoke Walk is a fitness movement that uses a weighted bar, called a yoke, to build strength and improve coordination It can be done alone or with a partner, and the weight of the yoke can be manipulated and adjusted to challenge the body over time The resistance provided by the bar is said to help improve mobility, posture, coordination and stability, while also promoting muscular gains

Front Cone Hops, also known as Hurdle Hops, is an explosive drill used to increase agility, coordination, and increase strength throughout the lower body It is performed by jumping two feet over and two feet back to a designated cone, while maintaining control and balance It is a great way to build speed, power, and agility while also working the legs, core, and balance

The Weighted Squat is a popular exercise that strengthens and develops the lower body, primarily focusing on the hamstrings, quadriceps, buttocks, and hips It is an effective total body workout and can be used as a tool for general fitness or as a part of a more aggressive power and/or weight training program The increased weight allows for a greater development of strength, balance, stability, and proprioception while also increasing muscle size and definition

Bench skip is a high intensity interval training (HIIT) exercise that involves jumping on and off a raised platform or bench while travelling forward It helps to burn calories quickly, improve muscle endurance and power, and improve motor skills It is also a great way to add variety and challenge to a workout routine

Backward Drag is a fitness movement that involves doing a traditional drag while walking backward on a treadmill This movement can help to strengthen and tone the legs, glutes, and core muscles while improving balance, coordination, and quickness

Sled Push is a form of resistance training that involves pushing a weighted sled along the ground with force It is an effective full-body exercise that increases both strength and endurance, and can be utilized in multiple formats to provide a challenging workout

Barbell Squat With Plate Slide is a functional fitness movement that strengthens and develops the legs, core, and arms This exercise requires you to stand with a barbell across your shoulders and grip a plate between both hands You then slide the plate down as you squat and push it back up as you rise to an upright position This engages the lower body muscles, improving balance, coordination, and flexibility, while also strengthening the upper body

The Suspended Split Squat is a great exercise to develop strength, balance, and stability It is an isometric core workout that targets the quads, hamstrings, glutes, and core muscles It involves balancing your weight on one foot while suspended in the air and performing a split squat This exercise can be done with a suspension trainer or just your own body weight

Movements: Intermediate Hip Flexor And Quad Stretch
